{"id":21246,"title":"[Recommendations for the use of diagnostic testing in low respiratory infections in children older than three months].","abstract":"Recommendations for the use of diagnostic testing in low respiratory infection in children older than 3 months were produced by the Groupe de Recherche sur les Avancées en Pneumo-Pédiatrie (GRAPP) under the auspices of the French Paediatric Pulmonology and Allergology Society (SP(2)A). The Haute Autorité de santé (HAS) methodology, based on formalized consensus, was used. A first panel of experts analyzed the English and French literature to provide a second panel of experts with recommendations to validate. Only the recommendations are presented here, but the full text is available on the SP(2)A website.","date":"2014-03-31","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24613479","annotations":[{"name":"Respiratory system","weight":0.815461,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Respiratory_system"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.809423,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Pulmonology","weight":0.700925,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pulmonology"},{"name":"Allergy","weight":0.549525,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allergy"},{"name":"Pediatrics","weight":0.530919,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pediatrics"},{"name":"English language","weight":0.462586,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_language"},{"name":"Respiratory tract infection","weight":0.453327,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Respiratory_tract_infection"},{"name":"France","weight":0.386172,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.325719,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Literature","weight":0.089122,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Literature"},{"name":"Record 